															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-gael" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2900720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2900720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250265" alt="Agent Gael" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2900720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-gael" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2900720); return false;" >Agent Gael</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566261088 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Aug 2019 00:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4335178">
									

<p>I hope they do, while the plain format is part of the charm, these images are not not only aesthetically pleasing, they're informative and are a bit more in-depth than just sorting them under &quot;Keter, Euclid or Safe&quot;.</p>
<p>Some Keters are only a danger to anyone unlucky enough to be immediately close by, and otherwise have a rather limited impact, while some Euclid SCPs would have world ending consequences if they're not controlled.</p>
<p>Ease of containment does not translate to importance of containment, and having a symbol to quickly show that is a good idea.</p>

							</div>

								
					
