					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250265" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;" >Decibelles</a></span> <span class="odate time_1566323980 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Aug 2019 17:59</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4335873">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Ease of containment does not translate to importance of containment, and having a symbol to quickly show that is a good idea.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Ease of containment is reflected in the containment procedures for the SCP article, the importance of containment is reflected in the rest of the document. I know the symbols are supposed to be an in-universe way of quickly showing that/out-of-universe flavor thing, but the SCP article format itself conveys all this information through its text. That's how the format works. So I don't quite think I agree with this point.</p>

							</div>

								
					
