			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4335927">
									

<p>I can’t see this being very versatile at all. It’s just harder to pace an article when you have a massive infodump at the beginning. It makes it super hard for an author to understand what’s going through a reader’s head with this. You have to think about the fact that people who understand the system in its entirety will be reading along with casual readers who don’t know what any of the terms mean.</p>
<p>Some will be going into the special containment procedures and description already knowing all of this background information, while others will have next to none.</p>
<p>This format makes it very difficult to have control over the information readers have as they go, which is a very important thing to have control over.</p>

